          <div class="facts-section__icon-wrap">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="facts-section__number">1985</span>
          <span class="facts-section__stat-label">Established</span>
          <div class="facts-section__accent"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="dual-section">
    <div class="dual-section__inner">
      <div class="dual-section__block dual-section__block--schedule">
        <h2 class="dual-section__heading">Residency Schedule</h2>
        <div class="schedule-table-wrap">
          <table class="schedule-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Rotation</th>
                <th>Y1</th>
                <th>Y2</th>
                <th>Y3</th>
                <th>Y4</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Inpatient Psychiatry</td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--high">6m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--med">3m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--low">2m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--min">1m</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Outpatient Psychiatry</td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--none">—</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--med">4m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--high">6m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--high">6m</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Emergency Psychiatry</td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--low">2m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--low">2m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--min">1m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--none">—</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Consultation-Liaison</td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--low">2m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--low">2m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--min">1m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--min">1m</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Child & Adolescent</td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--none">—</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--none">—</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--low">2m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--low">2m</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Electives</td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--low">2m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--min">1m</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--none">—</span></td>
                <td><span class="schedule-pill schedule-pill--low">2m</span></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dual-section__block dual-section__block--didactic">
        <h2 class="dual-section__heading">Didactic Overview</h2>
        <div class="didactic-accordion">
          <details class="didactic-item">
            <summary class="didactic-trigger">
              <span>PGY1</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="didactic-content">
              <p>The first year focuses on foundational psychiatric skills, including psychiatric interviewing, mental status examination, and basic psychopharmacology. Residents complete rotations in inpatient psychiatry, emergency psychiatry, and medicine.</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Introduction to Psychopharmacology</li>
                <li>Psychiatric Interview Techniques</li>
                <li>DSM-5 Diagnostic Criteria</li>
                <li>Medical Psychiatry</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="didactic-item">
            <summary class="didactic-trigger">
              <span>PGY2</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="didactic-content">
              <p>The second year expands clinical exposure with outpatient psychiatry, consultation-liaison, and subspecialty rotations. Didactics focus on evidence-based treatments and psychotherapy fundamentals.</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Advanced Psychopharmacology</li>
                <li>Cognitive Behavioral Therapy</li>
                <li>Psychodynamic Psychotherapy</li>
                <li>Consultation-Liaison Psychiatry</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="didactic-item">
            <summary class="didactic-trigger">
              <span>PGY3</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="didactic-content">
              <p>The third year emphasizes subspecialty training including child and adolescent psychiatry, addiction psychiatry, and geriatric psychiatry. Residents begin longitudinal outpatient clinics.</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Child & Adolescent Psychiatry</li>
                <li>Addiction Psychiatry</li>
                <li>Geriatric Psychiatry</li>
                <li>Forensic Psychiatry</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="didactic-item">
            <summary class="didactic-trigger">
              <span>PGY4</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="didactic-content">
              <p>The final year focuses on leadership, practice management, and advanced electives. Residents prepare for board certification and career transition.</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Practice Management</li>
                <li>Leadership in Psychiatry</li>
                <li>Board Preparation</li>
                <li>Advanced Electives</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="research-section">
    <div class="research-section__inner">
      <h2 class="research-section__heading">Research</h2>
      <div class="research-section__content">
        <p>Research is an integral component of our residency program. All residents complete a scholarly project during their training, with opportunities in clinical research, quality improvement, and medical education scholarship.</p>
        <p>Faculty mentors guide residents through hypothesis development, IRB approval, data collection, analysis, and manuscript preparation. Many resident projects have been presented at national conferences and published in peer-reviewed journals.</p>
        <p>Current areas of research focus include treatment-resistant depression, telepsychiatry outcomes, substance use disorders, and health disparities in mental health care.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pgy-section">
    <div class="pgy-section__inner">
      <h2 class="pgy-section__heading">Post-Graduate Year (PGY)</h2>
      <div class="pgy-section__content">
        <p>The term PGY (Post-Graduate Year) refers to the year of training following medical school graduation. Our four-year program takes residents from PGY-1 through PGY-4, with progressive responsibility and autonomy.</p>
        <p>Each year builds upon the previous, with increasing complexity of cases, greater independence in clinical decision-making, and expanded teaching responsibilities.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="salary-section">
    <div class="salary-section__inner">
      <h2 class="salary-section__heading">Salary & Benefits</h2>
      <div class="salary-section__grid">
        <div class="salary-section__table-wrap">
          <h3 class="salary-section__subhead">Annual Salary (2024-2025)</h3>
          <table class="salary-section__table">
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>PGY-1</td>
                <td>$62,000</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>PGY-2</td>
                <td>$64,500</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
